@startuml RideSharingService_Annotated

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam enum {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

title <size:18>Ride Sharing Service - Class Diagram (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Rider requests a ride, system finds nearest driver, trip starts, driver delivers, fare calculated."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE — RideSharingService
' ====================================================================
class RideSharingService <<Singleton>> {
    - pricingStrategy : PricingStrategy
    - driverMatchingStrategy : DriverMatchingStrategy
    - trips : Map<String, Trip>
    - {static} instance : RideSharingService
    - drivers : Map<String, Driver>
    - riders : Map<String, Rider>
    --
    + endTrip(tripId) : void
    + setDriverMatchingStrategy(strategy) : void
    + startTrip(tripId) : void
    + requestRide(riderId, pickup, dropoff, rideType) : Trip
    + registerRider(name, contact) : Rider
    + acceptRide(tripId, driverId) : void
    + registerDriver(name, contact, vehicle, location) : Driver
}

class RideSharingServiceDemo {
    + main(args) : void
}

note top of RideSharingService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Rider opens the app. Client only talks to
    this **Facade** (also a **Singleton** — one
    service instance). It coordinates everything:
    driver matching, trip management, pricing.
    Rider calls requestRide(pickup, dropoff, SUV)."
    **Patterns: Facade + Singleton | SRP, DIP**
end note

RideSharingServiceDemo --> RideSharingService


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: USER MODELS — User, Rider, Driver, Vehicle
' ====================================================================
class User {
    - tripHistory : List<Trip>
    - name : String
    - id : String
    - contact : String
    --
    + addTripToHistory(trip) : void
}

class Rider {
    --
    + onUpdate(trip) : void
}

class Driver {
    - vehicle : Vehicle
    - currentLocation : Location
    - status : DriverStatus
    --
    + onUpdate(trip) : void
}

class Vehicle {
    - model : String
    - type : RideType
    - licenseNumber : String
}

enum RideType {
    SUV
    SEDAN
    AUTO
}

enum DriverStatus {
    IN_TRIP
    OFFLINE
    ONLINE
}

class Location {
    - longitude : double
    - latitude : double
    --
    + distanceTo(location) : double
}

note top of User #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Core models.**
    "**User** is the base (name, id, history).
    **Rider** and **Driver** extend/relate to User.
    Driver has a Vehicle, a Location, and a
    DriverStatus (ONLINE/OFFLINE/IN_TRIP).
    Vehicle has a RideType (SUV/SEDAN/AUTO)."
end note

Driver --> Vehicle : has >
Driver --> DriverStatus : status >
Driver --> Location : current location >
Vehicle --> RideType : type >
Rider --|> User
Driver --|> User


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: DRIVER MATCHING — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface DriverMatchingStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + findDrivers(drivers, location, rideType) : List<Driver>
}

class NearestDriverMatchingStrategy {
    - MAX_DISTANCE_KM : double
    --
    + findDrivers(drivers, location, rideType) : List<Driver>
}

note left of DriverMatchingStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 3 - Find a driver.**
    "Rider requested a ride. How do we
    pick a driver? Could be nearest,
    highest-rated, cheapest..."

    "**Strategy Pattern** — matching
    algorithm is pluggable.
    NearestDriverMatchingStrategy
    finds drivers within MAX_DISTANCE_KM.
    Add RatingBasedStrategy? One new class."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

DriverMatchingStrategy <|.. NearestDriverMatchingStrategy
RideSharingService --> DriverMatchingStrategy : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: TRIP CREATED — Central Domain Object
' ====================================================================
class Trip {
    - status : TripStatus
    - id : String
    - driver : Driver
    - observers : List<TripObserver>
    - fare : double
    - currentState : TripState
    - pickupLocation : Location
    - dropoffLocation : Location
    - rider : Rider
    --
    + addObserver(observer) : void
    + assignDriver(driver) : void
    + endTrip() : void
    + notifyObservers() : void
    + setState(state) : void
    + startTrip() : void
}

enum TripStatus {
    COMPLETED
    ASSIGNED
    REQUESTED
    IN_PROGRESS
    CANCELLED
}

note top of Trip #FFCDD2
    **STEP 4 - Trip is created.**
    "requestRide() finds a driver, creates a Trip.
    Trip starts in REQUESTED state. This is the
    **central domain object** — it uses:
    - **State Pattern** (trip lifecycle)
    - **Observer Pattern** (notify rider + driver)"
end note

Trip --> TripStatus : tracks >
Trip --> Location : pickup/dropoff >
Trip --> Rider : for rider >
Trip --> Driver : assigned to >
RideSharingService --> Trip : manages >
RideSharingService --> Rider : registers >
RideSharingService --> Driver : registers >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: STATE PATTERN — Trip Lifecycle
' ====================================================================
interface TripState <<State>> {
    + request(trip) : void
    + start(trip) : void
    + assign(trip, driver) : void
    + end(trip) : void
}

class RequestedState {
    + request(trip) : void
    + assign(trip, driver) : void
    + end(trip) : void
    + start(trip) : void
}

class AssignedState {
    + request(trip) : void
    + assign(trip, driver) : void
    + end(trip) : void
    + start(trip) : void
}

class InProgressState {
    + request(trip) : void
    + end(trip) : void
    + start(trip) : void
    + assign(trip, driver) : void
}

class CompletedState {
    + request(trip) : void
    + end(trip) : void
    + start(trip) : void
    + assign(trip, driver) : void
}

note bottom of TripState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 5 - Trip moves through states.**
    "Without this, Trip has huge if-else blocks.
    **State Pattern** — each state is a class.
    RequestedState: can assign a driver.
    AssignedState: can start the trip.
    InProgressState: can end the trip.
    CompletedState: terminal."

    Requested -> Assigned -> InProgress -> Completed
    Any -> Cancelled

    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

TripState <|.. RequestedState
TripState <|.. AssignedState
TripState <|.. InProgressState
TripState <|.. CompletedState
Trip --> TripState : delegates lifecycle >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: OBSERVER PATTERN — Notifications
' ====================================================================
interface TripObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onUpdate(trip) : void
}

note right of TripObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 6 - Rider & Driver get notified.**
    "On every state change, Trip calls
    notifyObservers(). Both Driver and
    Rider implement **TripObserver**."

    "**Observer Pattern** — Trip doesn't
    know how to send notifications.
    Driver.onUpdate() updates driver status.
    Rider.onUpdate() shows status in app.
    Add SMS service? One new observer."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

TripObserver <|.. Driver
TripObserver <|.. Rider
Trip --> TripObserver : notifies >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: PRICING — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface PricingStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + calculateFare(pickup, dropoff, rideType) : double
}

class FlatRatePricingStrategy {
    - FLAT_RATE : double
    - BASE_FARE : double
    --
    + calculateFare(pickup, dropoff, rideType) : double
}

class VehicleBasedPricingStrategy {
    - RATE_PER_KM : Map<RideType, Double>
    - BASE_FARE : double
    --
    + calculateFare(pickup, dropoff, rideType) : double
}

note bottom of PricingStrategy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 7 - Trip ends, fare calculated.**
    "How much does the rider pay?
    Could be flat rate, vehicle-based,
    surge pricing..."

    "**Strategy Pattern** again. PricingStrategy
    is pluggable. FlatRate charges fixed price.
    VehicleBased uses per-km rate by RideType.
    Add SurgePricing? One new class."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP, LSP**
end note

PricingStrategy <|.. FlatRatePricingStrategy
PricingStrategy <|.. VehicleBasedPricingStrategy
RideSharingService --> PricingStrategy : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "We traced: rider requests ride -> system finds
    nearest driver (**Strategy**) -> trip created in Requested state
    -> driver accepts (Assigned) -> trip starts (InProgress) -> trip
    ends (Completed) via **State Pattern** -> rider & driver notified
    via **Observer** -> fare calculated via **Pricing Strategy**.
    4 patterns: **Facade/Singleton**, **Strategy** (x2), **State**, **Observer**."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | Rider calls RideSharingService.requestRide() | Facade + Singleton | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | User/Rider/Driver/Vehicle/Location models | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | System finds nearest available driver | Strategy (matching) | OCP, DIP |
    | 4 | Trip created in REQUESTED state | -- | SRP |
    | 5 | Requested -> Assigned -> InProgress -> Completed | State | SRP, OCP |
    | 6 | On each state change, rider + driver notified | Observer | OCP, SRP |
    | 7 | Trip ends, fare calculated by pricing strategy | Strategy (pricing) | OCP, DIP, LSP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Request + Match** = Steps 1-3 | **Trip Lifecycle** = Steps 4-5 | **Notify + Pay** = Steps 6-7 |  |
endlegend

@enduml
